VisualPlayer — distribution notice
===================================

VisualPlayer's own source code is licensed under Apache License 2.0
(see LICENSE.md).

However, distributed binaries of VisualPlayer link against and include GPL
components — notably a full-build FFmpeg (with x264/x265) and/or GPL builds of
mpv/libmpv. Because these are combined into a single distributed work, the
combined binary as a whole is distributed under the terms of the

    GNU GENERAL PUBLIC LICENSE, Version 3 (GPLv3)

The full text of the GNU GPLv3 is available at:

    https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt

This project is non-profit and open source. As required by the GPL, the
"Corresponding Source" for the combined work is made available: it is this
public repository. A link to obtain the source is shown in the application's
"Licenses" screen and shipped alongside installed binaries.

Note (per BLUEPRINT §18): GPL does not distinguish profit from non-profit. The
basis for using GPL components here is our commitment to copyleft (publishing
source), which this open-source project satisfies. Apache-2.0 is one-way
compatible with GPLv3; FFmpeg/mpv/x264/x265 are GPLv2-or-later and are therefore
treated as GPLv3 when combined.

Third-party component licenses are collected in the licenses/ directory and are
viewable in-app via the "Licenses" screen (the `licenses_list` command).

This notice is general guidance, not legal advice. Review applicable law in your
jurisdiction before distributing.
